issue.body:
Hi All,

How to run some script on a scheduled time? For ex: 
```js
// express.js
app.post('/run-job', (req, res, next) => {
    //req.body.date_time -> setup pm2 with some config but without daemon on this time
})
```

Thank you.

body:
My workaround while this isn't fixed:

1. Create a `bin/job` that will execute your script for example:

```javascript
#!/usr/bin/env node
const { exec } = require('child_process')

exec(process.argv.slice(2).join(' '), function (error, stderr, stdout) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(`exec error: ${error}`);
    return;
  }

  console.log(`stdout: ${stdout}`);
  console.log(`stderr: ${stderr}`);
})

// fake long running process
setInterval(() => {}, 1e6)
```

2. Then this is the process declaration:

```json
{
    "name": "cron_compute_midnight",
    "script": "./bin/job",
    "exec_mode": "fork",
    "args": "curl -s http://localhost/api/batch/compute",
    "cron_restart": "0 0 * * *"
  }
```

Obviously, if this issue were to be fixed the following would work:

```json
{
    "name": "cron_compute_midnight",
    "script": "curl",
    "exec_mode": "fork",
    "args": "-s http://localhost/api/batch/compute",
    "cron_restart": "0 0 * * *",
    "autorestart": false
  }
```
